.TH "ib_init_ah_from_mcmember" 9 "ib_init_ah_from_mcmember" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ib_init_ah_from_mcmember \- Initialize AH attribute from multicast member record and gid of the device.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ib_init_ah_from_mcmember
.BI "(struct ib_device *device "  ","
.BI "u8 port_num "  ","
.BI "struct ib_sa_mcmember_rec *rec "  ","
.BI "struct net_device *ndev "  ","
.BI "enum ib_gid_type gid_type "  ","
.BI "struct rdma_ah_attr *ah_attr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
RDMA device
.IP "port_num" 12
Port of the rdma device to consider
.IP "rec" 12
Multicast member record to use
.IP "ndev" 12
Optional netdevice, applicable only for RoCE
.IP "gid_type" 12
GID type to consider
.IP "ah_attr" 12
AH attribute to fillup on successful completion
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBib_init_ah_from_mcmember\fP initializes AH attribute based on multicast
member record and other device properties. On success the caller is
responsible to call rdma_destroy_ah_attr on the ah_attr. Returns 0 on
success or appropriate error code.
